    <h1><i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i> Form 990 Guide</h1>
    <p class="help-intro">Understanding the IRS Form 990 annual return.</p>
    
    <div class="help-block">
        <h2>What is Form 990?</h2>
        <p>Form 990 is the annual information return that most tax-exempt organizations must file with the IRS. It provides information about the organization's mission, programs, finances, and governance.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="help-block">
        <h2>Which Form Do You File?</h2>
        <table class="help-table">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Form</th>
                    <th>Gross Receipts</th>
                    <th>Assets</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>990-N (e-Postcard)</strong></td>
                    <td>$50,000 or less</td>
                    <td>Any</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>990-EZ</strong></td>
                    <td>Under $200,000</td>
                    <td>Under $500,000</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>990 (Full Form)</strong></td>
                    <td>$200,000 or more</td>
                    <td>OR $500,000 or more</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </div>
    
    <div class="help-block">
        <h2>Key Sections</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Part I</strong> - Summary (revenue, expenses, net assets)</li>
            <li><strong>Part VIII</strong> - Statement of Revenue</li>
            <li><strong>Part IX</strong> - Statement of Functional Expenses</li>
            <li><strong>Part X</strong> - Balance Sheet</li>
            <li><strong>Part VII</strong> - Compensation of Officers</li>
            <li><strong>Schedule A</strong> - Public Charity Status</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div class="help-block">
        <h2>How This App Helps</h2>
        <p>The Form 990 page pre-calculates many required figures:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Total Revenue by source</li>
            <li>Total Expenses by category</li>
            <li>Functional expense allocation</li>
            <li>Net assets calculation</li>
            <li>Officer compensation details</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div class="help-warning">
        <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i>
        <strong>Important:</strong> This app assists with data gathering. Work with a qualified accountant or tax preparer for actual filing.
